Some basic Linux commands are:
1) ls = It will display the list of files and the directories.
2) ls -l =Displays the details of files.
3) ls -la =It will display the hidden files as well.
4) pwd =present word directory(shows your current path.
5) cd .. = changes directory to the previous directory.
6) cd = changes directory to the next directory.
7) mkdir <filename> = Make directory(creates a new folder).
8) rm -r <filename> = removes/deletes a file.
9) uname -a = Displays the system details.
10) touch <filename> = Creates an empty file.
